nse schemas now use `envelope(SuccessSchema)`; all 4xx/5xx use `ErrorEnvelopeSchema`. Removed imports of `errorMessage` (from `api-errors.ts`) and `ErrorResponseSchema` / `OkResponseSchema` / `UsernameCooldownResponseSchema` (from `validators.ts`) — legacy helpers still live there for the cleanup iteration.\n180\t  - Renamed `catch (err)` bindings to `catch (fetchError|updateError|queryError|insertError)` to avoid shadowing the imported `err` helper.\n181\t  - Updated `backend/src/__tests__/profile.test.ts`:\n182\t    - Success assertions now destructure `.data` from envelopes (challenge/verify, `/profile/me`, `PUT /username`, `/public-profile/:userId` still unwrapped since that route converts in a later iteration).\n183\t    - 409 USERNAME_TAKEN: asserts `body.ok === false` + `body.error.code === \"USERNAME_TAKEN\"`.\n184\t    - 429 cooldown: asserts envelope shape, `body.error.code === \"USERNAME_COOLDOWN\"`, `retryable: true`, and `details.nextEditAvailableAt` present.\n185\t    - Invalid-format username tests: status 400 → 422 (both \"too short\" and \"missing body\"); `body.error.code === \"INVALID_USERNAME\"`; `details` is the Zod issue array.\n186\t    - `POST /confirm-tx` missing body: status 400 → 422; `body.error.code === \"VALIDATION_FAILED\"`.\n187\t    - Renamed the two \"returns 400 for ...\" tests to \"returns 422 for ...\" to match the new behavior.\n188\t  - Updated `backend/src/__tests__/profile-me-zeroed.test.ts`: `toMatchObject` now wraps the expected shape in `{ ok: true, data: {...} }`.\n189\t- **Verification**:\n190\t  - `pnpm typecheck:self` → exit 0\n191\t  - `pnpm lint:self` → exit 0\n192\t  - Targeted: `vitest run --config vitest.unit.config.ts src/__tests__/profile-me-zeroed.test.ts` → 1/1 passed\n193\t  - Targeted: `vitest run --config vitest.integration.config.ts src/__tests__/profile.test.ts` → 13/13 passed\n194\t  - Full unit suite (`pnpm vitest run --config vitest.unit.config.ts`) → 214/214 passed across 20 files\n195\t\n196\t## Iteration 9 — 2026-04-22T10:05:51Z — OK\n197\t- **Log**: iteration-009.log\n198\t\n199\t## Iteration 10 — 2026-04-22 — DONE\n200\t- **Item**: [routes] Convert `backend/src/routes/public-profile.ts` to envelope responses; update profile test coverage.\n201\t- **Changes**:\n202\t  - Rewrote `GET /{identifier}` in `backend/src/routes/public-profile.ts`:\n203\t    - Success → `ok(c, { userId, username, avatarUrl, heatMultiplier, stats, createdAt })`.\n204\t    - Missing profile → `err(c, 404, API_ERROR_CODES.NOT_FOUND, \"Profile not found\")`.\n205\t    - Lookup failure → `err(c, 500, API_ERROR_CODES.PRECONDITION_FAILED, \"Failed to fetch profile\")`.\n206\t    - Response schemas use `envelope(PublicPlayerProfileSchema)` for 200 and `ErrorEnvelopeSchema` for 404/500.\n207\t    - Removed imports of `errorMessage` (from `api-errors.ts`) and `ErrorResponseSchema` (from `validators.ts`) — legacy helpers still live there for the cleanup iteration.\n208\t    - Renamed `catch (err)` binding to `catch (lookupError)` to avoid shadowing the imported `err` helper.\n209\t  - Updated `backend/src/__tests__/profile.test.ts`:\n210\t    - `GET /public-profile/:username` success test: destructures `body.data` from envelope (`body.ok === true`).\n211\t    - `GET /public-profile/:user_id` success test: asserts envelope shape, accesses fields via `body.data.userId` / `body.data.username`.\n212\t    - `GET /public-profile/:identifier` 404 test: now asserts `body.ok === false` and `body.error.code === \"NOT_FOUND\"` (was `body.error === \"NOT_FOUND\"`).\n213\t    - The \"no wallet field\" test is text-based and continues to pass unchanged.\n214\t- **Verification**:\n215\t  - `pnpm typecheck:self` → exit 0\n216\t  - `pnpm lint:self` → exit 0\n217\t  - Targeted: `vitest run --config vitest.integration.config.ts src/__tests__/profile.test.ts` → 13/13 passed\n218\t  - Targeted: `vitest run --config vitest.unit.config.ts src/__tests__/waitlist-contract.test.ts` → 41/41 passed\n219\t  - Full unit suite (`pnpm vitest run --config vitest.unit.config.ts`) → 214/214 passed across 20 files\n220\t\n221\t## Iteration 10 — 2026-04-22T10:09:13Z — OK\n222\t- **Log**: iteration-010.log\n223\t\n224\t## Iteration 11 — 2026-04-22 — DONE\n225\t- **Item**: [routes] Convert `backend/src/routes/create.ts` (FlipYou public entry) to envelope responses; update endpoint-level FlipYou tests and the shared OpenAPI contract helper.\n226\t- **Changes**:\n227\t  - Rewrote all four FlipYou routes in `backend/src/routes/create.ts`:\n228\t    - `POST /create`: success → `ok(c, { transaction, matchPda, matchId, commitment, lastValidBlockHeight })`; `400 INVALID_REQUEST` for bad base58 wallet or non-pubkey wallet (preserves current HTTP status for malformed identifiers, per FR-11 \"400 or 422\" wording); `403 FORBIDDEN` for wallet/profile mismatch; `409 CONFLICT` for duplicate match PDA (both pre-insert and race-fallback paths, now retryable:true); `500 PRECONDITION_FAILED` for transaction-build failure. 422 declared for Zod-validation failures via the default hook.\n229\t    - `GET /history`: success → `ok(c, { rounds })`; no error responses needed (empty list is the documented success).\n230\t    - `GET /by-id/{matchId}`: success → `ok(c, round)`; `400 INVALID_REQUEST` for non-hex matchId; `404 MATCH_NOT_FOUND` for missing or wrong-game match.\n231\t    - `GET /verify/{pda}`: success → `ok(c, round)`; `404 MATCH_NOT_FOUND`.\n232\t  - All 2xx response schemas now use `envelope(SuccessSchema)`; all 4xx/5xx use `ErrorEnvelopeSchema`. Removed imports of `errorMessage` (from `api-errors.ts`) and `ErrorResponseSchema` (from `validators.ts`) — legacy helpers still live there for the cleanup iteration.\n233\t  - Renamed `catch (err)` bindings to `catch (buildError|insertError|entryError)` to avoid shadowing the imported `err` helper.\n234\t  - Updated `backend/src/__tests__/openapi-contract.test.ts`: added the same `unwrapEnvelope` helper used in the waitlist contract test, and rerouted `getJsonResponseSchema` through it so schema-descent checks see the inner `data` payload. Required because the `/flip-you/verify/{pda}` 200 body is now an envelope `oneOf`; the existing `resolveSchema` only unwrapped `allOf` / `anyOf`.\n235\t  - Updated `backend/src/__tests__/endpoints.test.ts` FlipYou suites:\n236\t    - `POST /flipyou/create` 200 test: destructures `body.data`, asserts `body.ok === true`; commitment length check moved onto `data.commitment`.\n237\t    - `POST /flipyou/create` 401 tests (missing / expired JWT): assert `body.ok === false` and `body.error.code === \"AUTH_REQUIRED\"`.\n238\t    - `POST /flipyou/create` 403 test: asserts `body.error.code === \"FORBIDDEN\"`.\n239\t    - `POST /flipyou/create` 409 collision test: asserts envelope shape, `error.code === \"CONFLICT\"`, preserved human-readable message.\n240\t    - Both rate-limit tests: assert `body.error.code === \"RATE_LIMITED\"`.\n241\t    - `GET /flipyou/verify/:pda` and `/by-id/:matchId` success tests: destructure `body.data`.\n242\t    - `GET /flipyou/by-id/:matchId` 404 test: asserts `error.code === \"MATCH_NOT_FOUND\"`.\n243\t    - `GET /flipyou/history`: asserts envelope `body.data.rounds === []`.\n244\t    - `POST /pot-shot/create` + verify/by-id for pot-shot left unchanged (pot-shot routes convert in iteration 12).\n245\t- **Verification**:\n246\t  - `pnpm -C backend typecheck:self` → exit 0\n247\t  - `pnpm -C backend lint:self` → exit 0\n248\t  - Targeted: `vitest run --config vitest.unit.config.ts src/__tests__/openapi-contract.test.ts` → 8/8 passed\n249\t  - Targeted: `vitest run --config vitest.integration.config.ts src/__tests__/endpoints.test.ts` → 14/14 passed\n250\t  - Targeted: `vitest run --config vitest.unit.config.ts src/__tests__/waitlist-contract.test.ts` → 41/41 passed\n251\t  - Full unit suite (`vitest run --config vitest.unit.config.ts`) → 214/214 passed across 20 files\n252\t\n253\t## Iteration 11 — 2026-04-22T10:18:22Z — OK\n254\t- **Log**: iteration-011.log\n255\t\n256\t